title: Sources: DeSean Jackson near deal to coach DSU
description: Former Philadelphia Eagles star wide receiver DeSean Jackson and Delaware State are finalizing an agreement for him to become the program's next head coach, sources told ESPN's Pete Thamel on Thursday.

title: Cowboys opt to shut down Lamb for rest of year
description: The Dallas Cowboys have ruled out star receiver CeeDee Lamb for the team's final two games because of an ongoing shoulder injury.
author: Todd Archer

title: Liverpool will 'stay humble' - but lead at top 'feels different'
description: Mohamed Salah says it "feels different" as Liverpool come from behind to beat Leicester and move seven points clear at the top.

title: Pereira outshines Amorim in battle of new Portuguese bosses
description: Wolves manager Vitor Pereira outshines Manchester United boss Ruben Amorim in the battle of two new Portuguese bosses.

title: Amorim: Man Utd are maybe in one of their lowest moments
description: Ruben Amorim has admitted Manchester United are suffering "maybe one of their lowest moments" and has called for everyone – including the exiled Marcus Rashford – to be "strong in the moment".

title: Cross and Chisnall suffer shock exits in marathon Ally Pally session
description: Dave Chisnall crashed out of the World Darts Championship after suffering a dramatic final-leg loss to Ricky Evans, while former world champion Rob Cross was also dumped out in a remarkable session at Alexandra Palace.

title: Live updates: Seahawks need a win to keep playoff hopes alive
description: In the last Thursday Night Football of the year, Geno Smith leads Seattle against Caleb Williams and the Bears. Get highlights and more here.

description: As we enter the penultimate week of the NFL season, Nate Tice and Charles McDonald are back to break down all the action from a festive—but somewhat underwhelming—set of Christmas games before deep diving on the most interesting matchups to look forward to this weekend.
